verses.text:
Hear, O ye kings; give ear, O ye princes;
I,  I, will sing unto Jehovah;
I will sing praise to Jehovah, the God of Israel.

¶     Awake, awake, Deborah;
    Awake, awake, utter a song:
    Arise, Barak, and lead away thy captives, thou son of Abinoam.

Out of Ephraim they whose root is in Amalek;
After thee, Benjamin, among thy peoples;
Out of Machir came down <i>[k]</i>governors,
 And out of Zebulun they that handle <i>[l]</i>the marshal’s staff.

And <i>[m]</i>the princes of Issachar were with Deborah;
  As was Issachar, so was Barak;
  Into the valley they rushed forth at his feet.
  By the watercourses of Reuben
  There were great resolves of heart.

¶  Blessed <i>[q]</i>above women shall Jael be,
  The wife of Heber the Kenite;
  Blessed shall she be <i>[r]</i>above women in the tent.

She put her hand to the tent-pin,
And her right hand to the workmen’s hammer;
And with the hammer she smote Sisera, she smote through his head;
Yea, she pierced and struck through his temples.

At her feet he bowed, he fell, he lay;
At her feet he bowed, he fell:
Where he bowed, there he fell down <i>[s]</i>dead.
